Steps:
1. Prepare cart (add item, set address, set shipment, set payment)
2. Execute: mutation { createOrderFromCart(cartId: CART_ID) { id number status } }
3. Verify order created

1. Send introspection query: { __schema { types { name } } }
2. Check if introspection is enabled/disabled
3. If enabled, verify no sensitive internal types exposed

1. Prepare cart through full checkout flow (addItem, addOrUpdateCartShipment with address and method, addOrUpdateCartPayment)
2. Execute: mutation { createOrderFromCart(cartId: CART_ID) { id number status } } — record returned order ID and number
3. Execute the SAME mutation again: mutation { createOrderFromCart(cartId: CART_ID) { id number status } }
4. Query orders list to count orders: query { orders(filter: "createdDate gt 2026-03-06") { totalCount items { id number } } }
5. Verify only 1 order exists for this cart

1. Create cart, add items, complete checkout setup
2. Execute createOrderFromCart mutation — record orderId
3. Attempt to add an item to the same cart: mutation { addItem(cartId: CART_ID, productId: PRODUCT_ID, quantity: 1) { id itemsCount } }
4. Attempt to query the cart: query { cart(storeId: STORE_ID, cartId: CART_ID) { id status itemsCount } }
5. Attempt changeCartItemQuantity on the converted cart

1. Create cart in USD: mutation { createCart(storeId: STORE_ID, userId: USER_ID, currencyCode: "USD", cultureName: "en-US") { id } }
2. Add multiple items (Product A and Product B) via addItem mutations
3. Query cart and record all prices in USD: items[].listPrice, items[].placedPrice, totals.subTotal
4. Switch currency by updating cart: mutation { changeCartCurrency(cartId: CART_ID, newCurrencyCode: "EUR") { id currency { code } items { productId listPrice { amount currencyCode } placedPrice { amount currencyCode } } totals { subTotal { amount currencyCode } } } }
5. Verify ALL monetary fields now use EUR
